'''Emmanuel George Cefai''' (born 1955) is a Maltese [[Doctor of Law]], [[poet]] and [[philosopher]]. His poems are published {{Citation needed|date=December 2016}}. In the philosophical field he is acknowledged within professional circles as ‘promising’.<ref>http://www.philosophysharing.org</ref> This is mainly due to the fact that, as yet, he has published very little of his intellectual production.

==Poetry==

Cefai’s poetry is mainly composed in English. His poems are regularly published in reputable sites and frequently acclaimed by connoisseurs {{Citation needed|date=December 2016}}. In August 2011 he published an [[ebook]] with a collection of forty selected poems.<ref>http://www.poemhunter.com/ebooks/redir.asp?ebook=50777&filename=emmanuel_george_cefai_2011_8.pdf</ref> His creative production, mostly unpublished, includes lyric and epic poetry, drama, and short stories{{Citation needed|date=December 2016}}.

==Philosophy==

Cefai began publishing writings about his philosophical interests in 1978 {{Citation needed|date=December 2016}}. Nevertheless, the greater part of his extensive philosophical works are, as yet, still unpublished, mainly due to editorial reasons {{Citation needed|date=December 2016}}. He has posted a few draft productions on his own website.<ref>emmanuelgeorgecefai.weebly.com</ref>

In 2014, Cefai published ''The Spirit of Metaphysics: A philosophical monograph on a logical theory of the universe'', of which he presented his conclusions to the [[Philosophy Sharing Foundation]] in April 2015.[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FttjSZql9UY]

